  <section>

    <!-- Ingredients -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <div>
          <div class="card-title">Ingredients</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingredients">
        <ul>
          <li>6 cups no-salt-added vegetable broth</li>
          <li>¼ teaspoon crumbled saffron threads</li>
          <li>2 tomatoes, halved</li>
          <li>½ cup extra-virgin olive oil</li>
          <li>24 small shishito peppers, stemmed</li>
          <li>1 large yellow onion, chopped</li>
          <li>6 garlic cloves, chopped</li>
          <li>2 red bell peppers, chopped</li>
          <li>2 teaspoons Spanish smoked paprika (pimentón)</li>
          <li>1 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
          <li>1 teaspoon kosher salt, plus more to taste</li>
          <li>1 pound fresh green beans, cut into 1-inch pieces</li>
          <li>¼ cup finely chopped flat-leaf parsley</li>
          <li>3 cups imported Spanish rice (Calasparra or Arborio)</li>
          <li>3 cups cooked or canned no-salt-added chickpeas, drained and rinsed</li>
          <li>2 cups spinach, chopped</li>
          <li>1 cup chickpea aioli (or vegan/traditional mayonnaise with 1 minced garlic clove)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Procedure -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <div>
          <div class="card-title">Procedure</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="procedure">
        <ol>
          <li>Preheat oven to 400°F.</li>
          <li>In a saucepan, combine vegetable broth and saffron. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and cover.</li>
          <li>Grate tomatoes over a bowl until only skin remains.</li>
          <li>Heat a large paella pan (or large skillets) over medium-high and add olive oil. When shimmering, sear shishito peppers; transfer to a plate.</li>
          <li>Add onion, garlic, and bell peppers to the pan and cook 6–8 minutes, until softened.</li>
          <li>Stir in smoked paprika, cumin, and salt; cook 30 seconds. Add green beans and cook until slightly softened.</li>
          <li>Add tomato pulp and parsley; cook 30 seconds, then stir in rice.</li>
          <li>Add broth, chickpeas, and spinach. Stir and cook until liquid is mostly absorbed, about 5 minutes.</li>
          <li>Nestle the shishitos on top and transfer pan to the oven. Bake uncovered 12–15 minutes until rice is al dente.</li>
          <li>Remove from oven, cover with foil, and let rest 10 minutes. Serve hot with aioli on the side.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

  </section>
